			<abstract>
<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><p>The single crystal of ThCr 2 Si 2 -type BaPd 2 As 2 was successfully prepared by a self-flux method, and the crystal structure was characterized by X-ray diffraction method with the lattice parameters a = 4.489(2) Å and c = 10.322(3) Å. Bulk superconductivity below a T c (critical temperature) of 3.85 K was revealed in this compound by the measurements of resistivity, magnetic susceptibility and specific heat, and this T c is much higher than those of other isostructural Pd-based superconductors.</p></div>
			</abstract>
		</profileDesc>
